attributeList.attribute: The interaction is tested in the presence of human tBid and liposomes that mimic the mitochondrial outer membrane composition.

In the absence of other proteins BAX was primarily present in a monomeric form. The presence of tBid or Bif1 (in this case accompanied by an increase in the temperature in which the experiment is performed) increased the amount of BAX in higher-order oligomeric forms.
